Stpes for Haskell Installation--->

1. Goto Haskell website
  https://www.haskell.org/platform/#linux-ubuntu

2. Select Operating System on which you wnat to install eg. Ubuntu, Fedora,Redhat etc

3. Click on Ubuntu

4. Type the command on terminal
    $ sudo apt-get install haskell-platform	   

5.  Go to your terminal again and run the GHCI command. 
   Once you get the Prelude prompt, you are ready to use Haskell on your local system.

6. To exit from the GHCI prolog, you can use the command ":quit exit".

7.
